{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1dad818a-df28-4fed-b711-8c6a27f1d346","content":"Use **`dotnet run`**, not `dotnet test`.\n\nThe `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HotReload` package works with the **Microsoft Testing Platform** runner, which is invoked via `dotnet run`. When you use `dotnet run`, the test host stays alive and watches for file changes, rerunning affected tests automatically.\n\n`dotnet test` uses the classic VSTest adapter and doesn't support the hot reload workflow.\n\n```bash\n# Make sure the env var is set, then:\ndotnet run\n```\n\nSince your project already has `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` enabled, `dotnet run` will launch the testing platform directly and hot reload will kick in.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e36d99a9-903c-4f9a-bdfc-287d32184d0d","outputTokens":159,"requestId":"7C26:D4E0A:289B248:2D096DD:69F94A72"},"id":"062e02ae-8fcd-4b84-bd25-73f5bf08f7b4","timestamp":"2026-05-05T01:40:07.537Z","parentId":"49c3e241-fa2b-4139-ae91-b2df249c7f82"}
